Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; then thinly slice crosswise into quarter-moons.

== Garden Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} and half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @pho stock concentrate{1}, @water{1%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until Step 6.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion, carrots, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; stir to combine. Cover and cook, stirring twice, until lightly browned and almost tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Uncover and stir in @peas{4%ounce}(tender-crisp) and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and water has completely evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and @pepper{pinch}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Fried Tofu ==

Halve @tofu{1%unit} crosswise, then halve each piece horizontally through the middle to make four thinner squares (eight squares for 4 servings). Pat dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @flour{1/2%cup}, @cornstarch{2%tablespoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{pinch}. Whisk in @cold water{1/3%cup}.

> TIP: If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat a 1/2-inch layer of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add tofu to bowl with batter. Gently turn to evenly coat on all sides. Once oil is shimmering, add coated tofu to pan. Cook until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== Assembly ==

Once rice is done, add veggies, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, half the scallion greens, and remaining @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} to #pot{}. Stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Sweet Chili Katsu Sauce ==

In a second #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @water{1%tsp}. Microwave until warm, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Halve each piece of tofu diagonally. Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with tofu. Drizzle with sauce and sprinkle with remaining scallion greens. Serve.